{
  "texts": [
    "Evaluation MethodologyTo objectively assess the effectiveness and educational value of the cyber exercise scenarios generated by LLM1 and LLM2, we employ a multidimensional evaluation framework.",
    "This framework consists of six key criteria: Details, Technical Soundness, Realism, Creativity, Usability in Exercises, and Expandability with Human Inputs.",
    "Each criterion is assigned a value between 0 to 5, where 0 represents the minimum and 5 the maximum score, to quantify the scenarios' attributes comprehensively.",
    "These factors ensure that exercises are realistic, engaging, and technically accurate, reflecting the complexity of real-world cyber threats.",
    "They enrich the creativity, encouraging learners to think critically and innovatively."
  ]
}